te real step definitions in each matching `.steps.js` file.\n\nSince the `common
.js` already defines many matching steps as empty functions, I can override them
in the specific step definition files by providing implementations before the co
mmon steps, or by creating custom step definitions.\n\nActually, `autoBindSteps`
will override common steps if the specific file defines them with the same patte
rn. Let me create comprehensive step definitions for each matching feature.\n\nB
ut wait - the BDD setup uses a mock NestJS app from `bdd-setup.js`, which curren
tly only sets up AuthModule and Profile controllers. It doesn\'t include the Mat
chingModule. So the BDD tests for matching would need either:\n1. A separate set
up that includes MatchingModule\n2. Or direct service testing\n\nLooking at the 
existing auth BDD steps, they make HTTP requests to the mocked server. For match
ing BDD tests to work properly, I\'d need to set up the matching module in the t
est app too.\n\nHowever, the review report says "BDD 验收测试步骤定义为空实现" a
nd asks to implement them. Let me check if there\'s already a way to include mat
ching in the BDD setup, or if I should create a more comprehensive bdd-setup tha
t includes matching.\n\nActually, looking at `bdd-setup.js`, it only imports Aut
hModule, ProfileController, PhotoController, etc. It doesn\'t have MatchingModul
e. I would need to modify `bdd-setup.js` or create a matching-specific setup.\n\
nBut wait - the review says to implement the step definitions, not necessarily t
o make all BDD tests pass in the current infrastructure. The BDD tests could als
o test the service directly.\n\nLet me look at how `auth-common.js` works - it u
ses `getServer()` which returns a supertest agent. For matching, I\'d need to ad
d the matching controllers to the test app or test the service directly.\n\nLet 
me check if there\'s a way to run BDD tests and what they look like.',
